==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scream
<hw>Scream</hw> <pr>(skr⟦emac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Screamed</conjf>
<pr>(skr⟦emac⟧md)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Screaming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Icel. <ets>skraema</ets> to
scare, terrify; akin to Sw. <ets>skr⟦aum⟧ma</ets>, Dan.
<ets>skraemme</ets>. Cf. <er>Screech</er>.]</ety> <def>To cry out with a
shrill voice; to utter a sudden, sharp outcry, or shrill, loud cry, as
in fright or extreme pain; to shriek; to screech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I heard the owl <qex>scream</qex> and the crickets cry.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>scream</qex> thyself as none e'er <qex>screamed</qex>
before.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scream</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scream
<hw>Scream</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sharp, shrill cry, uttered
suddenly, as in terror or in pain; a shriek; a screech.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Screams</xex> of horror.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Screamer</ent>⟦br⟧
